article.headline: Davidson 92, Georgia Southern 87
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. (AP) -- Logan Kosmalski, Ian Johnson and Brendan Winters each scored 19 points Saturday to lift Davidson past Georgia Southern 92-87, giving the Wildcats the Southern Conference's South Division title. Jason Morton added 16 points for the Wildcats (17-7, 13-0), who have won 12 straight games. Jean Francois scored 28 points for Georgia Southern (15-9, 8-4), while Terry Williams added 25. Davidson shot 49 percent for the game and went 30-for-39 from the free-throw line. The Wildcats led by as many as 17 points, but Georgia Southern cut the gap to 83-79 with less than five minutes to play. The Eagles were within 91-87 with 1:29 left, but couldn't get any closer.
